3. Rate Limiting: rate limiting software, such as rate-limiting libraries in programming languages
4. Content Security Policy (CSP): CSP implementation in web servers or CDNs
5. HTTPS: SSL/TLS certificates and implementations
6. Regular Security Audits: penetration testing tools, such as Metasploit or Burp Suite
7. CDN: content delivery network services, such as Cloudflare or Akamai
